news.title: Pune: Property tax arrears on hold for now
news.para: "The demand to introduce the tax discount will be considered only after a nod from the CM's office," said former leader of the House in PMC and BJP leader Ganesh Bidkar.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA razes illegal extension of flat in Gaur City
news.para: The move came after some residents made a complaint to the CEO of GNIDA Surendra Singh in a Jansunwai on Tuesday.

news.title: DDA approves allotment of EWS flats constructed at Jailorwala Bagh
news.para: There are about 1,640 households. Eligible households will be allotted these EWS flats through draw of lots. After rehabilitation of the eligible households of JJ cluster Jailorwala Bagh, the land so vacated measuring approximately 11,129 sqm will be disposed of by DDA through auction, it said.

news.title: DDA nod to allot 18 CWG flats to ministry of external affairs with discount
news.para: ​The decision was taken in a meeting of the urban body's highest decision-making body -- Authority -- chaired by Lt Governor V K Saxena, who is also the Chairman of DDA.

news.title: Mumbai: Illegal building's demolition starts but residents refuse to vacate
news.para: The building with 90 flats came up very quickly in 2018, but it was totally illegal. The issue was raised in the assembly, and ward officials were suspended. The residents who stand to lose their homes have exhausted their legal battle too.

news.title: Mumbai: Patra Chawl flat buyers take protest route to get homes
news.para: The Mhada-owned 46-acre property has been in the eye of the storm for the past four years after the original builder, Guruashish Construction, a subsidiary of HDIL, was unable to complete the rehabilitation project.

news.title: MCD rolls out new amnesty scheme related to unauthorised colonies, Lal Dora, other areas
news.para: ​As per this scheme, to be effective from September 15, taxpayers of residential properties in these colonies or areas are required to pay the property tax dues (only principal amount) for the financial years 2021-22 and 2022-23, and after this payment, all outstanding property tax dues prior to 2021-22 shall be waived off, the MCD said.

news.title: Major IT parks, posh villas top list of stormwater drain encroachers in Bengaluru
news.para: According to an Assistant Executive Engineer (Stormwater Drain-Mahadevapura zone) of the BBMP, Bagmane Techpark, Wipro, and Purva Paradise have encroached on drains across various survey numbers of Mahadevapura zone, which bore the brunt of the rain fury.

news.title: Gurugram: No new power connection for 15 months, Vipul World buyers go to DC
news.para: DHBVN has stopped issuing fresh electricity connections due to inadequate infrastructure. The developer is supposed to submit a bank guarantee of Rs 15 crores and hand over 500 square yards of land for a 33kV substation, after which the discom will issue new connections.

news.title: Gurugram: Structural audit to cover 200 towers in 17 societies
news.para: The structural audit, according to the department, will cover more than 200 towers covering an area of around 2.5 crore sq ft in 17 residential societies during the 45-day process.

news.title: Bombay HC may ask BMC to put all building project records online
news.para: The court said it "will need to revisit the law on several aspects once and for all". It listed issues they propose to address, including whether illegality in construction can be regularised.

news.title: Gurugram: Power infrastructure deficient, 25 societies may lose licences
news.para: In the absence of a proper connection due to incomplete electrical infrastructure, these societies are heavily dependent on diesel generators.

news.title: Delhi RERA orders DDA to register all ongoing e-auction schemes
news.para: Delhi RERA has said since about 150 of the 1,000 plots were left for auction by May 1, 2017, DDA is bound to register this scheme and any other scheme where it sells real estate assets after this timeline.

news.title: Chennai: Unwritten 'rate card' plays havoc with building budgets
news.para: If construction of a 1,500-sqft building costs `35 lakh, a minimum of another `5 lakh goes out as bribe to be paid at every stage of approval and construction. Bigger project attract equally bigger attention and bribe cost.

news.title: Vadodara: Public hearings on objections for town planning schemes on Sep 17
news.para: The TP scheme 58 in Vadadala has been proposed on an area of 389 hectares. The scheme includes 12 metre, 30 metre and 75 metre wide TP scheme roads. The civic body will get 7,31,556 square meter land for the roads.
